model.PDSC

Class PDSCTagChildrenException

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.PDSC.PDSCTagChildrenException

  • public class PDSCTagChildrenException
extends java.lang.Object
    Attribute exception represent exception for tag under certain conditions defined by PDSC standard. example : Tag if is parent is components have children: ... ... but if his parent is , tag have no children
    Author:
    Mirco Palese

        private java.lang.Integer exception
        The exception. 0 = only and only if tag is "tagX" and his parent his "tagY", "tagX" must NOT contain the specified child 1 = only and only if tag is "tagX" and his parent his "tagY", "tagX" must contain the specified child

      • description

        private java.lang.String description
        child's description Note that description it only make sense if exception is 1, if value of exception is 0 description will be completely ignored this value is stored in tag_children_exception table but is not saved in this class. it Is saved directly in new tag during query.

      • required

        private boolean required
        required Note that required it only make sense if exception is 1 exception is 0 required will be completely ignored. this value is stored in tag_children_exception table but is not saved in this class. it Is saved directly in new tag during query. default value is false
